This oil and gas exploration and production concern said it completed a common-share rights offering, under which it raised about 73 million Canadian dollars (US$62.1 million).
The company said that most of the proceeds would be used to redeem its Series B preferred shares and that the balance would be used to reduce debt.
As previously reported, for each common share held, Canada Northwest holders were offered one right to acquire an additional common share at C$4 each.
In Toronto Stock Exchange trading on Friday, Canada Northwest closed at C$4.15, up 10 Canadian cents on heavy volume of 322,712 shares. 

